title: [MinFirebaseApp] See why Employee cannot be fetched with id and updatedAt
message:
[MinFirebaseApp] See why Employee cannot be fetched with id and updatedAt

To reproduce:

1) Put the google-services.json file in the app folder
2) Start the app
3) Click on login to sign in anonymously
4) Click on "create employee", see that the employee is created
5) Go to console.firebase.google.com to check that the employee is
created with id, name and updatedAt
6) Click on "show employee" from the app, see the "updatedAt" and "id"
are not set.
7) Check the logcat to find something like "No setter/field for id found"

title: [loc8r] Implement locationsListByDistance
message:
[loc8r] Implement locationsListByDistance

It's part of Ch.6 of the book "Getting MEAN with Mongo, Express,
Angular, and Node".

Implement locationsListByDistance by using geoNear method of mongoose
model. Notice that the implementation does not use the
getDistanceFromRads and getRadsFromDistance methods as shown in the book
because the book probably has some inconsistent information. Since we
are parsing a GeoJSON to geoNear, the parameters should be in meters,
same as the distance from the output.

Fix some error handling code.

title: [go][concurrencyrace] Let everyone has a chance to get good food for each race
message:
[go][concurrencyrace] Let everyone has a chance to get good food for each race

Summary:
Let everyone has a chance to get good food for each race by getting a random
sleep before getting his/her food.

Remove the unnecessary "sync.Once" for getting the food.

Adjust the time duration, the text, and the number of people to make the
program a little bit more interesting.

Make sure history is done before the main program exits, so each line of code
in the program is guaranteed to be run (previously main exits before the
goroutine that prints out history can print that its done).

Test Plan:
Run the following a few times and see that everyone has a chance to get an
apple.
go run concurrencyrace.go
